    "definition": "The steering system must have positive steering stops that prevent the steering linkages from locking up (the inversion of a four bar linkage at one of the pivots). The stops:\na. Must prevent the wheels and tires from contacting suspension, bodywork, or Chassis during the track events\nb. May be placed on the uprights or on the rack"
